G-MOE-GPU4-PINNED — GPU residency rung 4: pinned staging + the LRU question answered (2026-07-02)
=================================================================================================
BUILT:
1. Pinned ping-pong staging (cuda_forward.cu): each streamed expert's 3 slices are staged
   into a pinned host blob (q36_stage_slice: codes + adjusted row_off built in-place +
   prec + bscale, 256-aligned) and shipped with ONE cudaMemcpyAsync per expert (pinned =
   truly async, overlaps GPU compute); ping-pong buffers with reuse-guard events
   (cudaEventSynchronize two experts back). Replaces 12 small pageable copies per expert.
2. Routing-locality telemetry (harness): per layer, how many of the NU selected experts
   repeat from the same layer's previous token.

GATE (35B OK-container, greedy 16, 25 resident + 15 streamed):
  SEQ IDENTICAL 21/21 — the EIGHTH arithmetic/transport regime unchanged.
  VERDICT: **GREEN**.

THE DESIGN ANSWER (why this receipt matters beyond the speedup):
  **LOCALITY = 32.6%** (2085/6400 selected experts repeat from the previous token).
  Expert routing on this model is LOW-locality -> an LRU expert cache would eliminate only
  ~1/3 of streams while adding eviction complexity and VRAM pressure. STREAMING is the
  right architecture for the rump; LRU is HEREBY NOT-WORTH-BUILDING on this evidence
  (revisit only if a workload shows >70% locality).

THE LADDER (16-token greedy, 35B-A3B GDN-MoE, i9-11900KB + RTX 2060 12GB):
  stateless O(n^2)           0.018 tok/s
  + state decode             0.165        9.1x
  + OMP rows                 1.136        6.8x
  + AVX2/dequant-free        1.605        1.41x
  + batch/parallel-if        1.655        1.03x
  + GPU dense resident       3.312        2.0x
  + GPU experts 25-26/40     3.824        1.15x
  + stream rump + threading  5.672        1.48x
  + pinned staging           **6.073**    1.07x    (~0.16s/token flat)
  CUMULATIVE                             **337x**

REMAINING HEADROOM (documented, not chased tonight): mmap first-touch page faults on cold
expert slices; a dedicated copy stream + event graph for full copy/compute overlap; CUDA
graphs over the per-layer kernel chain; and the REAL next deliverable — wire the qwen36
hybrid path into the served daemon (routes/launcher/one-config) so this ladder serves chat.
CONTEXT for scale: gemma4-12B production serves at 26 tok/s on this card; this is a 3x
bigger model at interactive speed via structural levers (A3B routing + OK packed residency
